<br>
Suggestion: Get rid of the 14 levelling forums, merge quest + epic quest, merge pet + epic pet and create an OT-forum. Oh, and while i am still on it: Get rid of that Planes of Power forum now as it basically turned into a general forum 2 (a mix of spell, skill and general discussions). <p><center><a href= "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3300" ><img src = "http://homepage.ruhr-uni-bochum.de/Michael.Kusnierz/Everquest/Pictures/blind.jpg"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=duftin>Duftin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(1/3/03 12:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8323.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cyas</span><hr size=1> I have to agree with you folks that there are too many forums, but I would have to disagree with abolishing the leveling forums.  I have found from reading this forum over that past 6 months that I cannot really participate in many of the discussions that happen in the general forum, because they pertain to mostly 60+ issues.  I am just now getting to level 50, and I gained a lot of insight from reading the leveling forums as I went through each spell circle.  If someone were to post about something, say, what to hunt in their 30's, it would get answered, but then quickly swallowed up by which 60+ summoned item affects pets more.  Right now that discussion means as much to me as what a level 30 should hunt means to you.  The information that many of you have contributed to during your respective risings to power is often invaluable to those of us hoping to follow in your footsteps.<br>
<br>
I think there is an opportunity to consolidate the forums, but as a person who relied on the leveling forums heavily for suggestions on how to get where I am, I humbly ask that they not be abolished so aspiring magi have the same chance to look for what to hunt from levels 24 to 28, as you folks have for hunting from 60 to 65.<br>
<br>
Duftin Fizzlefoot<br>
Proud Mage of the 50th Season<br>
Norraths Justice, Luclin Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilyana>Kilyana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#333333>(1/3/03 1:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8323.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   levelling forums</span><hr size=1> I agree. As a sub-60 mage, the separate levelling forums have been the most useful part of this board to me, and having each 14 of them makes it far easier to find information about where to go than any other class message board I've seen.<br>
<br>
My suggestion  would be leave the general forum the way it was, then when discussion has died down in General (or after a period of say, one week) move the topic to the correct forum. <br>
<br>
